cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their optimization for embedded GPUs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses model compression techniques, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates higher-level libraries for optimization, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the need for hardware-instructed neural network pruning, which could fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
